00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:38,357
According to the so-called Islamic system,
you have to give until you're broke.

193
00:18:38,357 --> 00:18:42,198
And Zakat (unintelligible) goes on, until
you're broke.

194
00:18:42,198 --> 00:18:43,768
(unintelligible)

195
00:18:44,503 --> 00:18:46,286
2.5%, one time.

196
00:18:46,286 --> 00:18:48,286
From anything when you receive it.

197
00:18:48,777 --> 00:18:50,225
At the time you receive it.

198
00:18:52,803 --> 00:18:58,117
Dr. Khalifa: Ok. Number 3 is that...

199
00:18:59,467 --> 00:19:00,301
A woman: Yeah.

200
00:19:01,038 --> 00:19:03,216
Dr. Khalifa: The Fasting we're doing in the month of Ramadan.

201
00:19:05,794 --> 00:19:11,353
And this, this goes a long way towards developing your soul.

202
00:19:13,353 --> 00:19:19,281
Dr. Khalifa: Because Siyam, Siyam, ROOZE, ROOZE, ROOZE?

203
00:19:19,281 --> 00:19:20,115
A woman (Speaking Farsi): ROOZE (Fasting)

204
00:19:20,115 --> 00:19:23,220
Dr. Khalifa: ROOZE (Fasting) during the month of Ramadan.

205
00:19:24,062 --> 00:19:29,172
Because every day in Ramadan, you're telling
your body "you're not gonna eat or drink until sunset."

206
00:19:30,962 --> 00:19:33,415
So, this, this straightens you.

207
00:19:34,213 --> 00:19:38,899
So, God gave us a wild horse. This body is a wild horse. We are supposed to tame it.

208
00:19:40,556 --> 00:19:43,292
So, God gave us the means to tame it and control it.

209
00:19:43,783 --> 00:19:47,624
Also, it's a measure of your degree of development.

210
00:19:48,851 --> 00:19:52,508
This will take me back to the Prayers, the Five Contact Prayers.

211
00:19:52,753 --> 00:19:58,865
Because you can measure your degree of development
by, for example, the Morning Prayer, which is before sunrise.

212
00:20:00,435 --> 00:20:02,643
It is very good for you physically, also.

213
00:20:04,546 --> 00:20:07,958
You will not develop arthritis if you do
wake up every morning before sunrise.

214
00:20:08,326 --> 00:20:12,091
I used to say this on a theoretical basis
until I heard the advertisement.

215
00:20:12,091 --> 00:20:15,872
Maybe, you also heard this from the Arthritis
Foundation.

216
00:20:16,332 --> 00:20:21,218
It says "do not stay in, in the same position, sit in the same position for a long time."

217
00:20:21,463 --> 00:20:25,243
Some truck driver was asking "what do I
do? I have arthritis."

218
00:20:25,611 --> 00:20:30,000
And they said "every few hours you must get
out and stretch."

219
00:20:31,105 --> 00:20:38,199
Now, when we go to sleep and we, we sit like that,
the joints become stiff. They need to be lubricated.

220
00:20:38,707 --> 00:20:47,060
So, God does not want to bother us and annoy
us by asking us to get up before sunrise every day.

221
00:20:47,919 --> 00:20:49,919
He doesn't need us to do that.

222
00:20:50,164 --> 00:20:51,305
We need it.

223
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:54,102
So, if we do the Morning Prayer...

224
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:59,354
I'm sorry I (unintelligible), but this is the physical part of it.

225
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:05,767
If you get up and lubricate your joints, and you
will not have arthritis when you grow up, (unintelligible).

226
00:21:07,635 --> 00:21:12,136
The spiritual part of it is you can measure
the degree of your development.

227
00:21:12,136 --> 00:21:19,498
Because as you become strong, you, not the
body, you become strong, your body will become obedient to you.

228
00:21:20,296 --> 00:21:23,646
So, you can measure if, if you wake up...

229
00:21:24,260 --> 00:21:27,733
If you cannot wake up at all in the morning,
you are in bad shape.

230
00:21:28,408 --> 00:21:36,790
You cannot tell your body to get up for your
own good, for the morning meal, the Morning Prayer before sunrise.

231
00:21:37,727 --> 00:21:41,146
Because there is a fight between you and your
body every morning.

232
00:21:41,146 --> 00:21:48,037
If you, if you decide to do this, there comes tomorrow
morning before sunrise and the body wants to sleep.

233
00:21:49,387 --> 00:21:54,026
But you need, you need to, to make it wake up.

234
00:21:55,560 --> 00:22:02,101
So, this struggle takes place and one of you
wins, either you or your body.

235
00:22:03,143 --> 00:22:07,601
If the body wins, you continue to sleep. And you will continue to be weak.

236
00:22:08,644 --> 00:22:14,326
If you win, you will grow and you develop and the growth of
the soul is very fast.

237
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,509
Sura 17

238
00:22:17,245 --> 00:22:18,386
It says "the growth..."

239
00:22:19,061 --> 00:22:22,841
See, we grow until we're 5 feet or 6 feet
tall.

240
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:27,291
But the soul grows until it is bigger than
San Francisco, the soul, your soul.

241
00:22:28,252 --> 00:22:31,518
So, the degree of growth is, the gain is fantastic.

242
00:22:32,745 --> 00:22:38,558
It's not like, you know, we eat this food
to grow and we're very limited in growth, the body is.

243
00:22:39,049 --> 00:22:40,804
But the soul grows immensely.

244
00:22:40,804 --> 00:22:46,670
So, if you succeed in, in forcing your body to
get up before sunrise and do the Morning,

245
00:22:46,670 --> 00:22:51,677
make contact with your Creator before sunrise,
you grow a lot.

246
00:22:52,413 --> 00:22:54,413
So, at first, it will be difficult.

247
00:22:55,149 --> 00:23:05,925
But in a month or two, you will grow sufficiently that when you say to your body "get up and do the Morning Contact Prayer", it will get up grudgingly.

248
00:23:07,398 --> 00:23:11,178
And this will show you another, the degree
of your growth.

249
00:23:11,546 --> 00:23:13,239
You will be on your way.

250
00:23:13,484 --> 00:23:18,245
It will be very good but then even though your body is getting up grudgingly to do the Contact Prayer, it's very good.

251
00:23:18,245 --> 00:23:21,779
Better than saying "no" and losing to your body.

252
00:23:23,462 --> 00:23:27,900
But gradually as you grow stronger, your body
will become absolutely obedient to you.

253
00:23:28,330 --> 00:23:30,403
This will tell you how much growth you attained.

254
00:23:32,613 --> 00:23:36,855
There comes a time before sunrise to set the alarm. In fact, you will not need to set the alarm anymore.

255
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,392
This is true. You will not need it.

256
00:23:40,397 --> 00:23:47,715
You will wake up your body at the right time
before sunrise to get up to do the Contact Prayer.

257
00:23:48,513 --> 00:23:51,863
And your body obediently will, will start to enjoy.

258
00:23:52,415 --> 00:23:56,317
And this will tell you at what degree, where you
stand.

259
00:23:58,121 --> 00:24:02,142
And eventually, you will really enjoy. You will be enjoying the Morning Prayer.

260
00:24:02,572 --> 00:24:06,352
You will be very cheerful. Most people get up in the morning and have a long face.

261
00:24:07,181 --> 00:24:11,096
But you'll get up with a big smile every
morning before sunrise.

262
00:24:12,630 --> 00:24:17,883
So, this will provide you with a yardstick
as to the degree of your growth.

263
00:24:18,435 --> 00:24:20,865
Now, Fasting does the same thing.

264
00:24:21,786 --> 00:24:25,259
Because first thing in the morning, your
body wants breakfast.

265
00:24:25,750 --> 00:24:33,089
And you issue a command to your body. "No, I'm not gonna eat or drink not until sunset."

266
00:24:33,089 --> 00:24:35,934
And this will cause you to grow and develop.

267
00:24:36,233 --> 00:24:37,895
So, God designed these things.

268
00:24:37,895 --> 00:24:43,966
Zakat also (unintelligible) you're taking, not your money, but most
people love very much, and you give it away.

269
00:24:45,391 --> 00:24:51,077
So, you can see that all these are designed
for, for our benefit to make our souls grow and develop.

270
00:24:51,077 --> 00:24:52,770
These are gifts from God.

271
00:24:53,138 --> 00:24:56,549
And if you are fortunate to receive the gift,
you will do these things.

272
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,743
It seems like what it takes is a decision.

273
00:25:02,743 --> 00:25:05,602
You decide that you want to worship God alone.

274
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:09,259
Then, God will give you these gifts and you'll be able to do it.

275
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:13,898
So, your part is really very easy. All you need to do is a decision.

276
00:25:14,723 --> 00:25:18,467
"I want to be redeemed. I want to be with God alone."

277
00:25:19,671 --> 00:25:24,243
"I believe that Muhammad, Jesus, Mary, Hussein,
Ali, none of them has any power."

278
00:25:24,979 --> 00:25:26,979
"Only God has all power."

279
00:25:26,979 --> 00:25:29,347
So, the question, this is all you need, a decision.

280
00:25:29,347 --> 00:25:33,495
And God, you'll see that you do these things
automatically.

281
00:25:37,852 --> 00:25:46,603
The fourth minimum, we call it ZIKR (ذکر).

282
00:25:53,722 --> 00:25:55,722
I just wrote it ZIKR (ذکر).

283
00:25:56,888 --> 00:25:58,336
But I have to explain it.

284
00:25:58,336 --> 00:26:01,502
In the Quran, there's a commandment, in the
Quran, that's very important that says,

285
00:26:01,502 --> 00:26:03,686
(33:41) يَٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُوا۟
[33:41]  O you who believe...

286
00:26:03,686 --> 00:26:07,588
(33:41) ٱذْكُرُوا۟ ٱللَّهَ ذِكْرًۭا كَثِيرًۭا
[33:41]  ... remember GOD continuously.*

287
00:26:07,588 --> 00:26:09,588
A lot. Frequently.

288
00:26:09,588 --> 00:26:17,173
And this is not any ritual or anything that
you perform. It's something that you do continuously.

289
00:26:17,418 --> 00:26:22,302
You look at this view and say "Subhan Allah." God be glorified.

290
00:26:23,591 --> 00:26:27,064
You realize God's creation, the beauty that
God created in the world.

291
00:26:27,064 --> 00:26:28,450
You look at the fruit.

292
00:26:28,695 --> 00:26:30,695
Look how many flavors we have here.

293
00:26:31,309 --> 00:26:34,720
When I say the word "orange", you think of a
certain flavor.

294
00:26:36,131 --> 00:26:38,131
Then, I say "strawberry."

295
00:26:38,376 --> 00:26:40,376
And you think of a certain flavor.

296
00:26:40,806 --> 00:26:46,304
Strawberry has a color, texture, taste, flavor,
smell.

297
00:26:46,549 --> 00:26:49,531
And these are all chemicals that God created in
the strawberry.

298
00:26:50,820 --> 00:26:51,961
There is peach.

299
00:26:52,513 --> 00:26:54,513
(unintelligible)

300
00:26:54,513 --> 00:26:57,188
So, when you look at this, you say, "Subhan Allah."

301
00:26:59,188 --> 00:27:00,820
And God didn't have to do all this.

302
00:27:01,188 --> 00:27:02,390
But this is ZIKR (ذکر).

303
00:27:02,820 --> 00:27:07,704
When we say "Subhan Allah", we think of God's
creation and God's Greatness.

304
00:27:07,704 --> 00:27:09,336
This is what we do with ZIKR (ذکر).

305
00:27:09,643 --> 00:27:11,643
But let me start from the beginning.

306
00:27:12,379 --> 00:27:16,957
The minimum that you want to set for yourself
is starts when you wake up in the morning.

307
00:27:16,957 --> 00:27:23,255
The first thing you must say in the morning
must be the name of God, first thing you say.

308
00:27:24,772 --> 00:27:30,000
In this country, most people start with a
dirty word in the morning, every morning, when the alarm goes off.

309
00:27:33,375 --> 00:27:35,375
You want to start with the name of God.

310
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:38,050
Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem

311
00:27:38,848 --> 00:27:40,234
La Elaha Ella Allah

312
00:27:40,234 --> 00:27:42,234
There is no god except the One God.

313
00:27:43,054 --> 00:27:49,754
It's gonna take you three or four months if you're not doing it already, it's gonna take you three or four months, at least, to get used to it.

314
00:27:51,227 --> 00:27:53,227
The first thing you do when you open up your
eyes.

315
00:27:53,227 --> 00:27:54,552
This is ZIKR (ذکر).

316
00:27:56,209 --> 00:28:00,296
Because what you utter, the first thing you
say in the morning, every morning, this is

317
00:28:00,296 --> 00:28:02,910
what you'll utter when you get up on the Day
of Resurrection.

318
00:28:03,708 --> 00:28:08,224
The real life, the eternal life, that will
determine your rank forever.

319
00:28:09,513 --> 00:28:13,600
And you don't wanna utter a dirty word on
the Day of Resurrection.

320
00:28:16,484 --> 00:28:19,711
So, this is the first thing we do, and of course, we do the Morning Prayer.

321
00:28:20,263 --> 00:28:28,952
There are certain commandments in the Quran, straightforward commandments, that you must do to carry out this, this gift.

322
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:35,928
For example, in Sura 18, God says "Do not say, I will do anything without saying IN SHAA ALLAH", saying "God willing."

323
00:28:36,726 --> 00:28:37,226
It says,

324
00:28:37,226 --> 00:28:39,840
(18:23) لَا تَقُولَنَّ لِشَا۟ىْءٍ
Do not say about anything

325
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:42,270
(18:23) إِنِّى فَاعِلٌ ذَٰلِكَ غَدًا
I'm doing this tomorrow

326
00:28:42,270 --> 00:28:45,743
(18:24) إِلَّآ أَن يَشَآءَ ٱللَّهُ
without saying IN SHAA ALLAH.

327
00:28:48,811 --> 00:28:53,389
You must never say "I'm gonna see you tomorrow" and that's it.

328
00:28:53,389 --> 00:28:55,389
You must say "I'll see you tomorrow, God willing."

329
00:28:55,880 --> 00:29:04,508
Even when you work with Americans, or non-Muslims,
at first, you'll be shy, they're (unintelligible) to say "what is this?"

330
00:29:04,508 --> 00:29:07,981
And they will say that. They'll be taken aback when you say "God willing",

331
00:29:07,981 --> 00:29:13,663
but eventually, they will respect you, and they
will get used to it, and you'll be carrying out your duty.

332
00:29:13,663 --> 00:29:16,154
You're actually reminding the people of their
Creator.

333
00:29:17,617 --> 00:29:20,494
Say "I'm gonna finish this at 6 o'clock,
God willing.

334
00:29:21,292 --> 00:29:24,851
And it must become a habit. Again, it'll take 3 or 4 months,

335
00:29:24,851 --> 00:29:26,913
but this is a commandment in the Quran.

336
00:29:26,913 --> 00:29:31,736
"Do not say, I will do anything without saying 'IN SHAA ALLAH.'"

337
00:29:33,571 --> 00:29:39,505
The Quran gives you a commandment, also, that
if you want to invoke protection for your children, for example,

338
00:29:39,505 --> 00:29:43,018
or your car, or your
property, you must say "Mã Shã Allãh."

339
00:29:45,719 --> 00:29:46,889
This is Sura 18, also.

340
00:29:46,889 --> 00:29:48,889
(unintelligible)

341
00:29:48,889 --> 00:29:51,380
This man who lost his garden.

342
00:29:51,380 --> 00:29:56,472
God says "if only when you entered your garden,
you said 'Mã Shã Allãh.' The complete statement is

343
00:29:56,472 --> 00:29:59,024
(18:39) مَا شَآءَ ٱللَّهُ لَا قُوَّةَ إِلَّا بِٱللَّهِ

344
00:29:59,024 --> 00:30:01,067
you would not have lost your garden.

345
00:30:02,648 --> 00:30:11,080
So, this tells us that in order to invoke protection
for your own children, your own property, your own car,

346
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:15,596
you say "Mã Shã Allãh." You start your car and starts like that, very
nicely, you say "Mã Shã Allãh."

347
00:30:16,229 --> 00:30:19,664
Now, before you start, say "Bismillah." (unintelligible)

348
00:30:20,585 --> 00:30:22,033
This is what ZIKR (ذکر) is.

349
00:30:22,845 --> 00:30:27,205
You must seek every chance to mention God.

350
00:30:27,935 --> 00:30:35,463
This is because we came to the realization, and this
is very important, that your god... who's your god?

351
00:30:35,463 --> 00:30:37,463
Let me stop you and ask you a question. Don't answer me.

352
00:30:38,138 --> 00:30:40,138
It's in your mind. In your mind.

353
00:30:40,629 --> 00:30:43,059
In your mind, answer me. Who is your god?

354
00:30:43,673 --> 00:30:47,269
So, every one of you is saying "my god is the
Creator of the heavens and the earth."

355
00:30:49,269 --> 00:30:51,514
And most of you are wrong.

356
00:30:53,514 --> 00:30:56,435
Shocked, we were shocked when we came to this realization.

357
00:30:57,846 --> 00:31:02,301
Two times. When we came to this realization, and I was
speaking and writing sermons.

358
00:31:02,731 --> 00:31:07,247
We were all shocked, because we examined ourselves
as to who is our god.

359
00:31:07,247 --> 00:31:11,149
Because it turns out, when you study the Quran
carefully, that your god

360
00:31:11,149 --> 00:31:15,000
is whoever or whatever occupies your mind most of the day.

361
00:31:16,473 --> 00:31:21,726
And we examined ourselves, and we found that
the Creator of the heavens and the earth was not our god.

362
00:31:22,831 --> 00:31:27,286
We thought we were believers, and we thought
our god was the Creator of the heavens and the earth.

363
00:31:27,593 --> 00:31:34,687
And this would have been the, and this is the answer that the Quran gives, describing many people, who are headed, going, going to Hell.

364
00:31:35,853 --> 00:31:42,087
At the end of Sura 23, for example, "if you ask them, who is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, and the Lord of the great dominion?"

365
00:31:45,192 --> 00:31:54,741
(23:86) قُلْ مَن رَّبُّ ٱلسَّمَٰوَٰتِ ٱلسَّبْعِ وَرَبُّ ٱلْعَرْشِ ٱلْعَظِيمِ
(23:87) سَيَقُولُونَ لِلَّهِ ۚ قُلْ أَفَلَا تَتَّقُونَ

366
00:31:55,241 --> 00:31:55,741
Why are you...

367
00:31:55,784 --> 00:31:56,741
[23:89]  ... "Where did you go wrong?"

368
00:31:57,171 --> 00:32:00,000
So, here, they are saying "God, the Lord of
the heavens and the earth."

369
00:32:00,552 --> 00:32:06,050
But you see, they are saying it with their mouth,
and this is the answer with their mouth,

370
00:32:06,050 --> 00:32:08,234
but they are preoccupied with other things.

371
00:32:10,234 --> 00:32:15,978
Therefore, this is why the commandment to
"remember constantly", is very important.

372
00:32:15,978 --> 00:32:18,653
At least, 51% of the day.

373
00:32:21,231 --> 00:32:27,588
And it's very easy, I know you're thinking, "how can I come? I'm at work, I'm busy with the computer, and so on. How can I think of God?"

374
00:32:28,999 --> 00:32:34,006
It's really very easy, because when you're go to the computer, you look, and you see somebody put a flower on the desk or something,

375
00:32:34,006 --> 00:32:35,454
you see flowers on your desk.

376
00:32:35,761 --> 00:32:39,234
You look at the design of the flower, you say "Subhan Allah." God be glorified.

377
00:32:40,155 --> 00:32:42,155
This will satisfy (unintelligible).

378
00:32:43,076 --> 00:32:49,310
This is why it will interrupt your, your thinking
and concentration of the world,

379
00:32:49,310 --> 00:32:51,310
and you'll, you'll, you'll think of God.

380
00:32:53,310 --> 00:32:55,310
By the way, I'll go back to the Contact Prayers.

381
00:32:55,310 --> 00:33:01,913
The Five Contact Prayers go a long way, towards,
this, remembering God.

382
00:33:01,913 --> 00:33:08,393
As a matter of fact, if you look at Sura
20, verse 14, God says,

383
00:33:08,393 --> 00:33:10,945
[20:14]  ... observe the Contact Prayers (Salat) to remember Me.

384
00:33:11,620 --> 00:33:13,620
(20:14) وَأَقِمِ ٱلصَّلَوٰةَ لِذِكْرِىٓ

385
00:33:13,620 --> 00:33:14,687
(unintelligible)

386
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:22,953
This is the reason, for giving you this gift, is to cause you to remember God, because it is not just the two minutes,

387
00:33:22,953 --> 00:33:25,751
you know, we
went back there and prayed the Afternoon Prayer, two minutes.

388
00:33:26,610 --> 00:33:32,108
It is not just those two minutes, that are
counted in your favor, as credit for you.

389
00:33:33,213 --> 00:33:37,238
Two hours ago, we looked at the watch, and
we said "oh, it's not the Afternoon Prayer yet."

390
00:33:38,036 --> 00:33:42,245
See, that's remembering God then, and this goes to
the credit.

391
